President Trump and German Chancellor Angela Merkel met with business leaders in the Cabinet Room to discuss workforce development and vocational training programs. Trump emphasized the importance of training American workers for manufacturing jobs in the 21st century and praised Germany's successful apprenticeship programs. The business leaders in attendance shared their own initiatives and programs aimed at training and employing American workers. Ivanka Trump also spoke, expressing her support for vocational education and workforce development. Vice President Mike Pence praised the participants for their innovation and commitment to strengthening the workforce in both the United States and Germany.